# CookieTI

A Cookie Clicker clone developed for the **TI-84 Plus CE** graphing calculator using the C SDK toolchain.

## рџЌЄ Features

- **Smooth Visual Animation:** Clicking the cookie triggers a scaling animation using double-buffered graphics (`libgraphx`).
- **BigNum Engine:** Supports arbitrary sized cookie counts using a custom scientific notation floating point format (`BigNum_t` structure), handling values far beyond the range of standard integer types.
- **Optimized Rendering:** Uses ZX0 compression to store the cookie sprite, minimizing the executable size.
- **TI-OS Float Integration:** Leverages the native TI calculator OS floating-point routines (`os_FloatToReal` and `os_RealToStr`) to print high-precision numbers on-screen without requiring standard library formatting overhead.

---

## рџ•№пёЏ Controls

- **`[ 0 ]`**: Click the cookie! Adds `0.01` cookies and triggers the squeeze/bounce animation.
- **`[ Mode ]`**: Exit the application and return to the home screen safely.

---

## рџ› пёЏ Compilation & Installation

### Prerequisites
You need the **CE C/C++ Toolchain** installed and added to your system path.
- [Download CE C/C++ Toolchain](https://ce-programming.github.io/toolchain/)

### Build Instructions
Open a terminal in the root directory of this repository and run:

```bash
make
```

Upon success, this will compile the project and create the executable file in the `bin/` directory:
- **`bin/COOKIETI.8xp`**

### Transfer to Calculator
Use **TI Connect CE** to transfer the `COOKIETI.8xp` file onto your TI-84 Plus CE.

Once on the calculator, run it via the `[prgm]` menu:
```text
pgrmCOOKIETI
```

