### Custom `BigNum` Implementation
Because standard C integers overflow quickly on 8-bit calculators, CookieTI uses a custom exponent format:
```c
typedef struct {
    double mantissa;
    int exponent;
} BigNum_t;
```
When values exceed `1e13`, they are normalized, incrementing the exponent. Numbers are formatted into the output string buffer as:
- Simple representation if exponent is `0` (e.g. `123`)
- Scientific representation if exponent is active (e.g. `123e+13`)
